<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution, habitat and conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Rehderodendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rehderodendron macrophyllum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rehderodendron macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from Hekou County, Yunnan Province, where three localities of the species (Binglangzhai, Tianweizhai and Shaba) have been documented since 1953. It was recorded as growing in evergreen broad-leaved forests along damp valleys and hillsides at 120-250 m elevation. The original habitat of 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. macrophyllum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">R. macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is severely disturbed by forestry activities. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Rehderodendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rehderodendron macrophyllum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rehderodendron macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Y. Wu &amp; K. M. Feng" authorityYear="1965" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Parastyrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Parastyrax macrophyllus" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Parastyrax macrophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was listed as Critically Endangered by the Chinese government in 2013 (
<bibRefCitation author="Ministry of Environmental Protection and Chinese Academy of Sciences" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" publicationUrl="http://www.mee.gov.cn/gkml/hbb/bgg/201309/W020130917614244055331.pdf" refId="B10" refString="Ministry of Environmental Protection and Chinese Academy of Sciences, 2013. China Biodiversity Red List-Higher Plants. Prepared by Ministry of Environmental Protection and Chinese Academy of Sciences, 1-691. http://www.mee.gov.cn/gkml/hbb/bgg/201309/W020130917614244055331.pdf" title="China Biodiversity Red List-Higher Plants. Prepared by Ministry of Environmental Protection and Chinese Academy of Sciences, 1 - 691." url="http://www.mee.gov.cn/gkml/hbb/bgg/201309/W020130917614244055331.pdf" year="2013">Ministry of Environmental Protection and Chinese Academy of Sciences 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Qin, HN" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="696 - 744" refId="B11" refString="Qin, HN, Yang, Y, Dong, SY, He, Q, Jia, Y, Zhao, LN, Yu, SX, Liu, HY, Liu, B, Yan, YH, Xiang, JY, Xia, NH, Peng, H, Li, ZY, Zhang, ZX, He, XJ, Yin, LK, Lin, YL, Liu, QR, Hou, YT, Liu, Y, Liu, QX, Cao, W, Li, JQ, Chen, SL, Jin, XH, Gao, TG, Chen, WL, Ma, HY, Geng, YY, Jin, XF, Chang, CY, Jiang, H, Cai, L, Zang, CX, Wu, JY, Ye, JF, Lai, YJ, Liu, B, Lin, QW, Xue, NX, 2017. Threatened species list of China's higher plants. Biodiversity Science 25 (7): 696 - 744" title="Threatened species list of China's higher plants." volume="25" year="2017">Qin et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). In 2020, we investigated its population, finding only three trees on the hill around Binglangzhai Reservoir, now a protected area. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Rehderodendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rehderodendron macrophyllum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rehderodendron macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still seriously threatened and research on the conservation biology of this species is urgently needed. The species flowers from November through January; the mature fruiting time is not known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
From the time of its original description until the present work, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Y. Wu &amp; K. M. Feng" authorityYear="1965" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Parastyrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Parastyrax macrophyllus" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Parastyrax macrophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been consistently placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W.W.Smith" authorityYear="1920" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Parastyrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Parastyrax" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Parastyrax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Flora Yunnanica</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Flora of China</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ming, TL" editor="Wu, CY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="406 - 438" refId="B9" refString="Ming, TL, 1983. Styracaceae. In: Wu, CY, Li, XW, Eds., Flora Yunnanica, vol 3. Science Press, Beijing: 406 - 438" title="Styracaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Yunnanica, vol 3." year="1983">Ming 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hwang, SM" editor="Editorial, Committee" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="77 - 150" refId="B5" refString="Hwang, SM, 1987. Styracaceae. In: Editorial, Committee, Ed., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae, vol 60, part 2. Science Press, Beijing: 77 - 150" title="Styracaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae, vol 60, part 2." year="1987">Hwang 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hwang, SM" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press &amp; Missouri Botanical Gardens Press, Beijing &amp; St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="53 - 271" refId="B6" refString="Hwang, SM, Grimes, J, 1996. Styracaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., Flora of China, vol 15. Science Press &amp; Missouri Botanical Gardens Press, Beijing &amp; St. Louis: 53 - 271" title="Styracaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China, vol 15." year="1996">Hwang and Grimes 1996</bibRefCitation>
). In the original description, Wu and Feng (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B15" refString="Wu, ZY, Li, XW, 1965. Yunnan Tropical and Subtropical Floristic Research Reports. Science Press, Beijing, 1-146. [In Chinese]" title="Yunnan Tropical and Subtropical Floristic Research Reports. Science Press, Beijing, 1 - 146. [In Chinese]" year="1965">Wu and Li 1965</bibRefCitation>
) indicated that its inflorescence is very short and its fruit is drupaceous with a fleshy 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“exocarp”">&quot;exocarp&quot;</normalizedToken>
(likely the mesocarp instead), which would be consistent with the characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W.W.Smith" authorityYear="1920" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Parastyrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Parastyrax" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Parastyrax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We re-examined the original material, including the paratype collection 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cai Ke-Hua 533</emphasis>
(KUN [acc. # KUN0026239!]), which possesses the only fruit gathered of the material cited in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B15" refString="Wu, ZY, Li, XW, 1965. Yunnan Tropical and Subtropical Floristic Research Reports. Science Press, Beijing, 1-146. [In Chinese]" title="Yunnan Tropical and Subtropical Floristic Research Reports. Science Press, Beijing, 1 - 146. [In Chinese]" year="1965">Wu and Li 1965</bibRefCitation>
). We found that the fruit of this collection is clearly immature, so its internal structure, which would otherwise help to confirm the placement of the species to genus, could not be determined. In March 2020, we conducted fieldwork in Binglangzhai, the type locality of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. macrophyllus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="macrophyllus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">P. macrophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There, we discovered plants that possess the same vegetative features as those in the type material of the species, yet with fruit in which the endocarp has many irregular rays intruding into the mesocarp, as in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Rehderodendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rehderodendron" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rehderodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Morphology of Rehderodendron macrophyllum and R. macrocarpum Hu. A-D Rehderodendron macrophyllum A branchlet and leaf B fruiting branch C young fruit D transverse section of fruit showing endocarp with many rays intruding into the mesocarp E fruit transverse section of R. macrocarpum. (Photographs: A-D by Wan-Yi Zhao from Hekou, Yunnan, China E by Wan-Yi Zhao rom Wawushan, Sichuan, China)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.161.54970.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456653" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">4D, E</figureCitation>
) and unlike in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. lacei" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="lacei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">P. lacei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(W.W.Sm.) W.W.Sm., the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W.W.Smith" authorityYear="1920" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Parastyrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Parastyrax" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Parastyrax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On this basis, we conclude that 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. macrophyllus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="macrophyllus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">P. macrophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is best placed in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Rehderodendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rehderodendron" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rehderodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W.W.Smith" authorityYear="1920" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Parastyrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Parastyrax" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Parastyrax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be redefined on characters that exclude those of 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. macrophyllum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">R. macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; we include diagnostic characters for this purpose in Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Key morphological differences amongst Rehderodendron, Pterostyrax and Parastyrax. N / A = not applicable." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/E11D813F309823053DE08EE2C91BEF56" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" tableUuid="E11D813F309823053DE08EE2C91BEF56">1</tableCitation>
, based on several previous studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, WW" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="231 - 236" refId="B12" refString="Smith, WW, 1920. Notes on certain Asiatic Styracaceae. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 12: 231 - 236" title="Notes on certain Asiatic Styracaceae." volume="12" year="1920">Smith 1920</bibRefCitation>
; 
