<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="W. Y. Zhao, P. W. Fritsch &amp; W. B. Liao" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Styracaceae" genus="Rehderodendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rehderodendron macrophyllum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rehderodendron macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. truongsonense" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="truongsonense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">R. truongsonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
P.W.Fritsch, W.B.Liao &amp; W.Y.Zhao (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. A lectotype of Rehderodendron macrophyllum (Yu Ping-Hua s. n. [KUN (acc.  KUN 0026237)] B isotype of R. truongsonense (Ulf Swenson, Do Van Truong, Hoang Manh Quyen &amp; Sylvain Razaflimandimbison 2131 [P 00937133])." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.161.54970.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456652" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">3B</figureCitation>
), a species distributed in northern and central Vietnam (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhao, WY" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="157 - 171" publicationUrl="http://www.diva-portal.org/smash/get/diva2:1345125/FULLTEXT01.pdf" refId="B16" refString="Zhao, WY, Fritsch, PW, Do, VT, Fan, Q, Yin, QY, Penneys, DS, Swenson, U, Liao, WB, 2019. Rehderodendron truongsonense (Styracaceae), a new species from Vietnam. Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 13: 157 - 171, http://www.diva-portal.org/smash/get/diva2:1345125/FULLTEXT01.pdf" title="Rehderodendron truongsonense (Styracaceae), a new species from Vietnam." url="http://www.diva-portal.org/smash/get/diva2:1345125/FULLTEXT01.pdf" volume="13" year="2019">Zhao et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). These two species share such features as evergreen tree; inflorescences axillary, congested and densely stellate-pubescent; bracteoles foliaceous, elliptic or obovate; filaments connate at base; and style pubescent. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. macrophyllum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">R. macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. truongsonense" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="truongsonense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">R. truongsonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by larger leaf blades 12-27 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-12(-15) cm (vs. 6-13 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-7 cm), with a greater number of lateral veins on each side (8-14 vs. 4-7).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In the protologue, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Yu Ping-hua s.n.</emphasis>
, a flower gathering deposited in KUN, was indicated as the type. Of the three sheets comprising this collection, KUN0026238 and KUN0026237 were stamped as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“TYPUS”">&quot;TYPUS&quot;</normalizedToken>
and KUN0026236 as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“ISOTYPUS.”">&quot;ISOTYPUS.&quot;</normalizedToken>
A short annotation is present on KUN0026237, so we have chosen this sheet (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. A lectotype of Rehderodendron macrophyllum (Yu Ping-Hua s. n. [KUN (acc.  KUN 0026237)] B isotype of R. truongsonense (Ulf Swenson, Do Van Truong, Hoang Manh Quyen &amp; Sylvain Razaflimandimbison 2131 [P 00937133])." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.161.54970.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456652" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">3A</figureCitation>
) as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
